==English==

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|uncork||}}

# To open (a bottle or other container sealed with a cork or stopper) by removing the cork or stopper from.<!--cork or stopper, because some wine bottles now have plastic "corks", but the word "uncork" is still applied to them-->
#:'''''uncork''' a bottle of wine''
# To release a powerful force.
#:''His suggestion '''uncorked''' a whirlwind.''
# {{baseball}} To make a strong throw or hit a ball hard.
#:''He '''uncorked''' a perfect throw to the plate.''

